comment:
My question is "How did you know?"

I'm not a fan of anyone... But I am very curious... Cause the fans, or the so called fans keeping moving back & forth between Johnny and Amber.
Whenever the evidence that present in a favor of anyone, they switch faster than a turtle flip himself from a turn over.
And people keep saying the same shits... "I know the truth, Cancel Amber". Ironically how a few weeks ago, they said the almost exact same thing "I know the truth, Cancel Johnny."

And I'm curious is because... I've dealt at close hand with divorce like theirs. It's happened to my befriends, both husband & wife are my befriends.
My childhood friend. I've known them my whole life. Do you know Johnny or Amber anymore than their screen times and what's the tabloid wrote about them? I think not.

And being so close to my friends... I still don't know shit. They been divorced a couple years, still talk bad about each other... And each play a victim while other opposite are the aggressor.

But I personally can't decide, I know my friend (husband) to be beater when's he drunk, he's beating people before, including his own dad. But I also know that my friend (wife) is a manipulative bitch and very good at driving people around her mad. So....

If anything, they both deserve each other. I think Johnny & Amber give each other just as good/bad as they got from one another. Nothing more, nothing less.

comment:
Legal battle with Johnny Depp, *NOTHING!*  Long before she met Mr. Depp, in *2009,*  Amber Heard was *arrested* for the *domestic assault* of her then partner, Tasya van Ree.   The domestic assault occurred in front of two police officers, and an international airport full of people.  Ms. van Ree confirmed to the arresting officers that she wanted Ms. Heard arrested.  Amber Heard did not protest the arrest.  She was booked and spent the night in jail.  At her arraignment the next day (an audio recording survives) Ms. Heard again does not protest her arrest.  Because the domestic couple live in another state, the Judge and the Prosecutor agree to hold the case open for a period of *two years* in case Ms. van Ree decides she wishes to press charges, or Ms. Heard reoffends.  When Ms. Heard met Mr. Depp, she attempted to expunge the record of this arrest.  When the press uncovered the story, Ms. Heard suborned *HER VICTIM* to release a false statement that attempted to clear her name.  Her lies were exposed when the arresting officer, Officer Beverly Leonard, came forward, and gave an interview.  

It should be noted that Johnny Depp *has never been arrested for, or charged with domestic assault.*  The "restraining order" that Ms. Heard so proudly displays was a *TEMPORARY RESTRAINING ORDER* , obtained *without the need to provide proof.*  It is an emergency precaution provided for immediate protection--until the Judge can hear the evidence in the case.  When Ms. Heard's case was reviewed, the Judge *DISMISSED THE CASE WITH PREJUDICE!*  This means that the Judge found Ms. Heard's case to be "egregiously flawed and without merit," and Ms. Heard *can never bring these charges against Mr. Depp in the future.*

If Mr. Depp has lost his role in the Fantastic Beasts franchise, in the middle of ongoing litigation concerning domestic abuse...then Amber Heard *SHOULD NEVER BEEN ALLOWED TO PLAY MERA IN AQUAMAN.*  She was already an arrested abuser.  Warner Brothers is making a public statement that *domestic abuse is fine as long as it is a woman assaulting another woman.*

Emilia Clarke should definitely take over the part of Mera in Aquaman 2.  She is a better actor and person.  Warner Brothers will eventually suffer the full effect of the destructive fallout surrounding Mr. Depp's cases.  Judge Nicol, whose son works for News Group Newspapers with Dan Wooton (both of whom Mr. Depp is suing), and whose wife is personal friends with Amber Heard's council, Jennifer Robinson, should have recused himself from the case.  Any Judge who feels justified to dismiss the evidence of *four police officers* , CCTV evidence, Doctor's affidavits, witnesses, and the audio tape confession of the accused...and find in favor of an admitted liar and arrested domestic abuser, without a *single piece of physical evidence* (no police reports, no doctor's statements, no medical records...), and only one single witness (the woman's *sister* ) who will testify that she saw Mr. Depp hit Ms. Heard *ONCE* , should be removed from the bench.  To the ultimate shame of Judge Nicole, Ms. Heard *will* reveal herself.  Narcissistic abusers don't just stop.  She will continue her abuse until someone is severely injured or killed.  Meanwhile, we can only hope that there is a court in Britain that is actually concerned with *EVIDENCE* , that will hear Mr. Depp's appeal.  The judgement in the Virginia Trial will have less concern with personal affiliations, and more concern with evidence and the law.
